      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Word Finding — Solve Any Rack in the Chat</h2>

      <p>Sometimes you are mid-conversation with Lex about strategy and you want to quickly check what words you can make from a set of tiles. You do not need to navigate back to the main solver. Just type your tiles directly in the chat — something like "What words can I make from AEILNRT?" — and Lex returns the results right there in the conversation.</p>

      <p>This is especially useful during coaching sessions. Lex might be reviewing your Daily Rack performance and you want to explore a specific combination. Or you are practising in the Dojo and want to verify an answer. The word-finding capability is always available, woven naturally into whatever conversation you are having.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ No Context Switching</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Stay in the chat. No need to open a new tab, navigate to the solver, type your tiles again, then come back. Ask Lex and get answers inline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Natural Language</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Ask however you want: "words from QZXJK", "what can I make with these tiles?", "solve AEIOU??". Lex understands all formats.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Automatic Word Identification</h2>

      <p>As you chat with Lex — whether you are reviewing games, running drills, or asking strategy questions — it automatically identifies words that are worth learning. These are words that appeared in your games, came up during training, or are relevant to the topic you are discussing. Lex highlights them as candidates for your Memory WordBench.</p>

      <p>This passive learning layer means every conversation doubles as a vocabulary session. You do not need to actively hunt for new words to memorise. Lex surfaces them naturally, explains why they matter (high score, unusual letter combination, common bingo stem), and suggests you add them to your study list. Over time, this builds a personalised vocabulary that reflects your actual playing patterns and weak spots.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">✓ Passive Vocabulary Building</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Every coaching session, every Dojo drill, every strategy discussion — Lex is quietly identifying words you should know. It <span class="text-white font-medium">highlights them during conversation</span> and explains their value. No extra effort required from you — just chat normally and your word list grows.</p>
